Here's our key verse for today verse six Let your speech always be with grace seasoned with salt disappeared That you may know how you ought to answer each one This is the word of God for the people of God Amen, they got at his blessing to the reading of his words.

01:00.081 --> 01:00.882
You may be seated

01:08.738 --> 01:11.200
Our theme verse back up on the screen for you.

01:13.583 --> 01:17.066
Yesterday morning, Christine and I were going through some old emails.

01:17.506 --> 01:21.090
I mean, from way back when we first met.

01:21.811 --> 01:27.276
And we're hadn't met face to face yet, but we're talking and sending emails back and forth.

01:27.296 --> 01:31.720
And we're just kind of nostalgic and watching how the relationship developed.

01:31.740 --> 01:37.906
And then over the years, how things have kind of matured and changed in the conversation.

01:38.082 --> 01:53.123
It's interesting, if you've ever done that, or gone back and looked at things, how memory's not quite right on how it actually happened, or what was the context, and you've just kind of got a general idea of it.

01:53.543 --> 01:55.946
And we were going back and we said, I don't remember that.

01:56.547 --> 01:57.689
I don't remember that either.

01:57.869 --> 01:59.391
Oh, I forgot about that.

02:00.232 --> 02:01.935
But one thing was consistent.

02:02.716 --> 02:07.282
And that is that in every conversation,

02:07.554 --> 02:11.098
I always felt safe and that she was like coming home.

02:12.099 --> 02:18.807
Now, for me, I had lots of relationships before her, but none of them ever felt like coming home.

02:19.948 --> 02:20.949
There was no home from me.

02:20.969 --> 02:22.391
I didn't even know what home was.

02:23.372 --> 02:27.316
And when I finally found out what it was, I didn't want to let it go.

02:27.336 --> 02:36.146
I think people have different kinds of presences.

02:36.898 --> 02:40.723
If you know what I mean when you're in with them, you can discern it real quickly.

02:41.905 --> 02:46.831
So a person you can laugh around, you feel more open with and honest with, you kind of pick up on that.

02:47.412 --> 02:55.243
And that's kind of a relationship that you just feel safe, like you're able to be who you are.

02:55.703 --> 03:03.794
And then there's this kind of relationship, and you know how real quick where their tone's harsh, they seem kind of judgmental, and you can't really

03:03.938 --> 03:07.702
Say anything without feeling like, I wonder if they're going to jump at me for saying that.

03:08.103 --> 03:10.145
And you know immediately you don't really feel safe.

03:10.485 --> 03:14.770
There's people like that as well and it doesn't take long to figure it out.

03:15.151 --> 03:24.842
You know that kind of person when you're with them some kind of tightens up inside and you go, you kind of guarded the whole time and when you walk out you go, I can breathe again.

03:24.882 --> 03:27.825
You ever had that in a relationship with something?

03:27.845 --> 03:28.626
I don't mean like

03:29.282 --> 03:30.263
a good relationship.

03:30.283 --> 03:33.947
I mean, connecting with someone or being around them made you feel that way.

03:35.769 --> 03:36.990
If it's me, I'm sorry.

03:41.615 --> 03:44.237
But their tone can be sharp, criticism all the time.

03:44.277 --> 03:46.379
There's tension, it's thick the whole time.

03:46.720 --> 03:49.322
I'm going to get into a story here in a little bit about that.

03:50.003 --> 03:56.690
But in my life, I walked away from a lot of toxic relationships really quickly because I didn't feel safe.

03:57.986 --> 04:05.938
I wouldn't even let the relationship get started because I'd already see warning signs and I'd been bitten too many times to say, yes, let's try this.

04:07.280 --> 04:10.485
With Christine, I never felt unsafe and never had.

04:10.646 --> 04:12.809
She's still home and will always be home.

04:13.570 --> 04:17.216
That's just one of those things that happens.

04:17.236 --> 04:20.481
And so safe and healthy relationships got me thinking.

04:21.502 --> 04:26.450
What would a safe and healthy church that feels like home be like?

04:27.202 --> 04:28.644
What kind of atmosphere would it be?

04:28.664 --> 04:36.416
What kind of a presence would we need to have to make sure our church feels like home to anybody who walks in?

04:37.358 --> 04:42.205
And as I thought about that, the church is healthy, it's positioned to grow.

04:42.245 --> 04:53.042
I've been in a lot of different worship services over the years, and I've seen a lot of churches where I didn't feel at home, and I've been in churches where I have.

04:53.723 --> 04:55.826
And I remember this one church in particular

04:56.098 --> 04:59.844
Down in Florida, I'll go down there for a few weeks every January.

05:00.485 --> 05:02.427
And I go to the same church because I liked it.

05:02.948 --> 05:06.834
But they did something there that I'd never see any other church do.

05:07.495 --> 05:13.003
They had this big old eelor sitting on the stage next to the podium.

05:14.205 --> 05:16.188
I mean, these things, you can't miss it.

05:16.208 --> 05:18.672
It was like three feet, one of the biggest ones they could find.

05:18.932 --> 05:25.522
And they stuck it there and I was curious about it, but they put an explanation in the bulletin why it was there.

05:26.306 --> 05:33.677
They said Eor was there because of a conversation that he had had with Winnie the Pooh on a blustery day.

05:34.539 --> 05:44.294
You might remember the story where Eor got swept up in the storm and started going down this creek on his back, kind of floating his demise.

05:44.795 --> 05:50.103
And who is on the bridge going, oh Eor, that's good to see you.

05:50.543 --> 05:52.486
And Eor kind of responds like this.

05:53.027 --> 05:54.770
Well, you know,

05:55.138 --> 05:57.321
It's not a problem I could use some rescue.

05:59.264 --> 06:04.450
And so Eor was on their stage to remind everybody we all need rescuing.

06:05.272 --> 06:10.979
Jesus saves us from our sin and he helps us and heals us.

06:11.139 --> 06:14.324
And he called his church like a hospital.

06:15.585 --> 06:25.138
And he said we are a spiritual hospital and everybody here is one level of triage or another depending on how serious their situation is.

06:25.282 --> 06:27.885
But everybody has something God can heal.

06:28.946 --> 06:30.308
And I thought, man, that's great.

06:30.328 --> 06:31.069
I liked that.

06:31.449 --> 06:35.073
And every time I went, I'd see or it was near Disney.

06:35.093 --> 06:41.380
So I thought at first when I thought, well, it's Florida, Disney, yeah, but nothing to do with Disney.

06:41.460 --> 06:46.406
It was all about Jesus and the healing culture they wanted to provide to people.

06:46.866 --> 06:50.130
And the church was growing because of that mindset.

06:52.706 --> 06:56.270
Like I said, I was safe there and I went as often as I could.

06:56.330 --> 07:01.617
When we go to church, you know, we don't just come to a service.

07:01.897 --> 07:03.399
We have an expectation.

07:03.919 --> 07:07.083
We have an expectation of what the atmosphere is going to be like.

07:07.744 --> 07:14.592
We know pretty much what people are going to say or how we're going to feel and we like that.

07:15.533 --> 07:19.538
And we know that because it's comfortable and it feels like home.

07:22.402 --> 07:33.574
And it's interesting to me, when we walk in, no matter what's going on on the outside world, when we walk in here, our expectation hopes change because we don't got here.

07:34.235 --> 07:36.918
And there are people who love us here, and we're cared for.

07:37.679 --> 07:40.182
And in this place, we find that hope.

07:40.202 --> 07:45.788
And out there, we don't know that we'll find that in a work a day world around us.

07:49.913 --> 07:51.154
What I'm talking about

07:51.554 --> 07:52.355
is atmosphere.

07:53.557 --> 08:03.469
That expectation that when you walk in, there will be smiling faces of people you know and friends and family and relatives pretty much everywhere in the place.

08:04.831 --> 08:06.273
And that's a good feeling for me.

08:06.393 --> 08:09.437
I know it is for most of us, if not all of us.

08:09.957 --> 08:19.890
So when a church starts to grow and new people start coming in, it can reveal underlying tones that aren't resolved as they are met ahead of time.

08:20.386 --> 08:31.520
So we'll talk about some of those tones on how it can create and keep a good atmosphere even when folks come in that are new or have never been a part of our culture here.

08:34.704 --> 08:42.595
The kindness that people meet at the door needs to be expressed throughout the entire culture, not just at the door.

08:43.255 --> 08:45.959
We can never become unsafe.

08:45.979 --> 08:48.402
We need to always be a safe place for people.

08:50.786 --> 08:51.768
Now, let me tell you this.

08:51.868 --> 08:54.231
A safe church doesn't mean it's soft.

08:55.233 --> 08:58.138
We talk about sin, but we don't browbeat about it.

08:59.079 --> 09:04.868
We talk about holiness, but we don't weaponize it and tell people, you're not holy, you need to shape up your ship out.

09:04.888 --> 09:05.670
We don't do that.

09:06.190 --> 09:07.152
That's not safe.

09:07.593 --> 09:10.056
What we do is a little different than that.

09:10.097 --> 09:15.165
A safe church is grace-filled and truth-centered.

09:16.627 --> 09:18.610
People can grow without being shamed.

09:19.522 --> 09:23.007
They can confess without being crushed.

09:24.088 --> 09:36.645
They can be healed without being watched and they can serve without being used and they can belong without being labeled.

09:38.247 --> 09:39.709
That's a healthy and safe church.

09:41.692 --> 09:42.573
We have that here.

09:42.593 --> 09:45.717
I want you to know that we have that here.

09:46.038 --> 09:48.081
This is not like we got to fix this thing.

09:48.641 --> 09:49.202
We have it.

09:49.826 --> 09:53.733
You just need to be aware that we have it and keep doing it and doing it well.

09:54.494 --> 09:55.456
Because that's important.

09:59.222 --> 10:05.053
I'm so thankful for that too because we would have a whole different sermon today if that wasn't true.

10:08.258 --> 10:12.806
But we have to be intentional about what we do when being safe as a church.

10:13.808 --> 10:15.090
It starts with leadership.

10:15.266 --> 10:16.528
It doesn't mean just me.

10:16.788 --> 10:19.892
It means anybody in a position of leadership sets the culture of the tone.

10:20.633 --> 10:27.742
And everybody here in leadership sets that tone with love and kindness and grace and spirit of cooperation.

10:27.982 --> 10:29.744
It is such a wonderful thing to see.

10:30.385 --> 10:41.819
And everybody in the church comes together, helps each other, and works together over and over again, because about family, it's about community.

10:42.280 --> 10:43.922
And when people have sensed that,

10:44.130 --> 10:45.671
And they see that it's real.

10:45.712 --> 10:47.353
They want to be a part of that.

10:48.214 --> 10:50.997
And so we got to continue to be intentional about being that way.

10:55.421 --> 11:02.668
As we position for growth, when people come in, we need to acknowledge the atmosphere that we have.

11:05.130 --> 11:05.831
And I'll tell you why.

11:06.351 --> 11:08.733
Because you, atmospheres are intentional.

11:09.174 --> 11:09.734
They're built.

11:09.794 --> 11:13.618
You can't assume it's going to continue without being intentional about it.

11:14.018 --> 11:15.480
And how do we focus it?

11:15.620 --> 11:16.621
How do we make it happen?

11:17.062 --> 11:20.666
The Apostle Paul says in Ephesians 4.29 the following words.

11:21.867 --> 11:30.057
Let no corrupt word proceed out of your mouth, but what is good for necessary edification, that it may impart grace to the hearers.

11:30.517 --> 11:41.490
Or as it says on this screen, let your speech always be with grace, season with salt, that you may know how to answer each person with grace and with truth.

11:45.506 --> 11:54.897
The words Paul uses, both here in Colossians, and when I just read out of Ephesians 4.29, are words of construction.

11:56.118 --> 12:01.204
They're words that are tools to help us with construction.

12:01.825 --> 12:08.513
Now, part of construction sometimes requires taking down what doesn't belong.

12:08.993 --> 12:10.995
Turn down a stronghold, for example.

12:11.616 --> 12:13.298
And if you're not sure what I mean by that,

12:13.570 --> 12:21.342
A stronghold could be something that's there that you're protecting that doesn't need to be there because it doesn't serve a use anymore.

12:21.983 --> 12:30.836
Could you imagine if people say, well, I love that old life way building in 99 buffet and whatever else it was before that and after that.

12:31.157 --> 12:34.502
And when it was Spirit of Halloween, I really love that building.

12:34.802 --> 12:35.824
So don't tear it down.

12:35.864 --> 12:37.847
Just put bass pro shops in there.

12:38.889 --> 12:39.710
Could you imagine?

12:40.110 --> 12:41.513
That would be a strong mobile.

12:41.553 --> 12:42.514
What do we do?

12:42.658 --> 12:45.901
we want to put something brand new in its place.

12:45.921 --> 12:49.585
As soon as it was announced, the next day that thing's almost all the way gone.

12:50.426 --> 12:56.511
So you know, they're going to put a new foundation, a solid foundation for something brand new.

12:56.992 --> 13:02.477
You can't build in something that doesn't serve the purpose for what's going to be there.

13:02.998 --> 13:11.506
So our words, when we see something that we need to help grow, sometimes we have to look at strongholds and help remove them.

13:12.034 --> 13:15.699
Now we're not telling folks, you know you've got a strong hold, you need to fix that.

13:15.979 --> 13:16.880
It's not like that.

13:16.900 --> 13:21.567
What we're saying is we believe God has something better for you.

13:23.389 --> 13:26.833
We want to help you figure what that is and won't put you along that journey.

13:27.354 --> 13:29.377
And I think that's the culture we have here.

13:30.198 --> 13:35.625
And I think that's what we talk about when we talk about helping people and loving people well.

13:36.967 --> 13:39.410
This is something that I don't have to

13:40.034 --> 13:41.476
Say, we ought to do this.

13:41.556 --> 13:48.563
I'm saying we continue to do this and continue to do it well with good intention in our heart.

13:48.583 --> 13:52.648
Because our words, our speech is rarely neutral.

13:54.570 --> 13:56.972
It's either building or it's tearing down.

13:57.873 --> 14:09.746
Now, the tearing down in this sentence could be destructive, but sometimes, like I said, some things have to be removed, torn down to build something good.

14:10.722 --> 14:15.910
But there's always the idea that if I'm going to tear something down, I want to put something better in its place.

14:16.851 --> 14:24.162
Otherwise, if I'm tearing down something with my words, with no antenna putting something better in its place, I don't need to say it.

14:24.783 --> 14:26.947
Because that will not help someone to grow.

14:28.769 --> 14:35.059
So if you want to know how to tell what the atmosphere of a church is, there's an easy way.

14:35.660 --> 14:39.666
Listen to a conversation in the parking lot before or after service.

14:40.962 --> 14:42.524
What are people talking about?

14:42.944 --> 14:45.127
Are they talking about what people wore?

14:45.447 --> 14:49.231
Are they talking about whether the preacher was too fat or too short?

14:49.711 --> 14:51.353
What are they talking about, right?

14:52.935 --> 14:54.837
They might be talking about leadership.

14:55.257 --> 15:03.787
They might be talking about somebody who's new came to church that they are about other churches or something like that, not about how people struggle.

15:04.267 --> 15:08.332
And if they're talking about struggles of people, are they talking about solutions?

15:08.792 --> 15:10.514
Are they talking about the problem?

15:10.882 --> 15:11.764
the person is.

15:13.146 --> 15:16.692
And you get to understand the culture from those conversations.

15:18.135 --> 15:26.108
So we listen to see if they're seeking solutions to a situation and ministry opportunity.

15:26.729 --> 15:32.359
Are they just talking about issues that they can't do anything about and refuse to?

15:33.040 --> 15:34.763
That's how you tell a culture of a church.

15:35.104 --> 15:36.306
It's not the sermon.

15:38.274 --> 16:06.514
Atmospheres aren't created by sermons alone They're created by habits and habits become conversations and conversations create culture and mindsets And I'm so Encouraged by the culture of our church here because after services we're talking about what we want to do for God We were talking about what we want to do to help people how they can minister and

16:06.722 --> 16:14.735
And that excites me because I've been in places before where after service we're going, what do you do about them folks?

16:16.017 --> 16:19.963
And that conversation was just this heartening.

16:20.865 --> 16:22.327
But here we're not doing that.

16:22.728 --> 16:25.332
We're saying, hey, how can we help people?

16:25.452 --> 16:26.194
What can we do?

16:26.574 --> 16:29.038
What can we do that we're doing now to do it even better?

16:29.098 --> 16:30.180
How can we reach more?

16:30.661 --> 16:33.906
Those kind of conversations are a church that wants to grow.

16:34.082 --> 16:37.605
It has a ministry mindset, and this church is just like that.

16:40.909 --> 16:50.978
I think, as I've said several times this year, we're on the precipice of God positioning us for a great moment and season of growth.

16:51.699 --> 16:56.584
We have the right mindset, all we have to do is get ready for that.

16:56.824 --> 16:58.245
And that's what this year is all about.

16:58.826 --> 17:03.090
And what these sermons are about is giving us a line to make sure we're all

17:03.362 --> 17:05.104
together on the same page.

17:08.507 --> 17:12.831
The Apostle Paul says our words must impart grace to the hearers.

17:14.313 --> 17:21.419
Maybe season was salt, but it isn't just preached, it's transmitted.

17:21.479 --> 17:32.530
In the message, the verse in Ephesians 4-29 says, watch the way you talk, say only what helps, because each word

17:32.802 --> 17:33.543
is a gift.

17:34.984 --> 17:39.568
Treat each word you say as a gift to someone else, as a blessing.

17:41.310 --> 17:42.491
